<title>Personal history of Jan Plat (he leaves Calvinia with Dia!kwain)</title>
<summary>An account of Jan Plat&apos;s movements with his travelling companion, Dia!kwain, and his meeting with his wife, who was keeping sheep in Louriet. A further account of Jan Plat&apos;s travels with Dia!kwain and the farmer Louw, whose sheep Dia!kwain had been keeping. Jan Plat states that Dia!kwain went with Louw to Kenhardt and then to the Free State.</summary><comments>1) p.6046e v: Lloyd does not find Dia!kwain&apos;s journey to the Free State improbable as he had told her that he thought that his sons might be there, 2) This story is found in Book VII-1</comments><date>9 January 1884 (started)</date><storypages>6046d-6046f</storypages><category>History (personal)</category><category>Relations with others</category><author>Jan Plat</author><keyword><kw>Jan Plat</kw><subkw>the personal history of</subkw></keyword>
